gomodel:SYNGO_4626  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Figure 6. GluRs show a developmental change of expression in outer hair cells. The apical turn (a) and basal turn (b) of whole-mount rat cochleae at P8 were used.\"\n\n\"Similar to GluK1, GluK3 is expressed in afferent terminals in the apical turn (E), but is diminished in the basal turn (F).\"\n\nIn outer hair cells, GluK3 (GRIK3) is expressed in the basal turn in early development but completely lost in adult (O).\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Temporal bones of Sprague-Dawley rats (4-6 weeks old or postnatal day (P) 8) were quickly removed and fixed in 2% paraformaldehyde for 10 min at room temperature, if not otherwise specified (Grati et al., 2012). Cochlear tissues were then dissected\"\n\nantibodies;\nPSD-93 (Alomone labs, 1:200)\nGluK3 (Synaptic Systems, 1:200)\nanti-GluK3 is a affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal antibody; the immunogen was a recombinant protein of amino acids 845-919 (C-terminus) of rat GluK3.\nGluK3 antibody produces a clean western blot with a single, wide band around the predicted size, using the synaptosomal fraction (P2) of rat" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4626" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

